7 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
8 // ----
9 // This pass moves instructions into successor blocks when possible, so that ----
10 // they aren't executed on paths where their results aren't needed. ----
11 // ----
12 // This pass is not intended to be a replacement or a complete alternative ----
13 // for an LLVM-IR-level sinking pass. It is only designed to sink simple ----
14 // constructs that are not exposed before lowering and instruction selection. ----
15 // ----
16 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----

206 /// Postpone the splitting of the given critical ----
207 /// edge (\p From, \p To). ----
208 /// ----
209 /// We do not split the edges on the fly. Indeed, this invalidates ----
210 /// the dominance information and thus triggers a lot of updates ----
211 /// of that information underneath. ----
212 /// Instead, we postpone all the splits after each iteration of ----
213 /// the main loop. That way, the information is at least valid ----
214 /// for the lifetime of an iteration. ----
215 /// ----
216 /// \return True if the edge is marked as toSplit, false otherwise. ----
217 /// False can be returned if, for instance, this is not profitable. ----
218 bool PostponeSplitCriticalEdge(MachineInstr &MI, ----
219 MachineBasicBlock *From, ----
220 MachineBasicBlock *To, ----
221 bool BreakPHIEdge); ----
222 bool SinkInstruction(MachineInstr &MI, bool &SawStore, ----
223 AllSuccsCache &AllSuccessors); ----
224 ----
225 /// If we sink a COPY inst, some debug users of it's destination may no ----
226 /// longer be dominated by the COPY, and will eventually be dropped. ----
227 /// This is easily rectified by forwarding the non-dominated debug uses ----

229 void SalvageUnsunkDebugUsersOfCopy(MachineInstr &, ----

271 /// Return true if a target defined block prologue instruction interferes ----
272 /// with a sink candidate. ----
273 static bool blockPrologueInterferes(const MachineBasicBlock *BB, 0
274 MachineBasicBlock::const_iterator End, ----
275 const MachineInstr &MI, ----
276 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI, ----
277 const TargetInstrInfo *TII, ----
278 const MachineRegisterInfo *MRI) { ----
279 for (MachineBasicBlock::const_iterator PI = BB->getFirstNonPHI(); PI != End; 0
280 ++PI) { 0
281 // Only check target defined prologue instructions ----
282 if (!TII->isBasicBlockPrologue(*PI)) 0
283 continue; 0
284 for (auto &MO : MI.operands()) { 0
285 if (!MO.isReg()) 0
286 continue; 0
287 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
288 if (!Reg) 0
289 continue; 0
290 if (MO.isUse()) { 0
291 if (Reg.isPhysical() && MRI && MRI->isConstantPhysReg(Reg)) 0
292 continue; 0
293 if (PI->modifiesRegister(Reg, TRI)) 0
294 return true; 0
295 } else { ----
296 if (PI->readsRegister(Reg, TRI)) 0
297 return true; 0
298 // Check for interference with non-dead defs ----
299 auto *DefOp = PI->findRegisterDefOperand(Reg, false, true, TRI); 0
300 if (DefOp && !DefOp->isDead()) 0
301 return true; 0
302 } ----
303 } ----
304 } ----
305 ----
306 return false; 0
307 } ----

309 bool MachineSinking::PerformTrivialForwardCoalescing(MachineInstr &MI, 0
310 MachineBasicBlock *MBB) { ----
311 if (!MI.isCopy()) 0
312 return false; 0
313 ----
314 Register SrcReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
315 Register DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
316 if (!SrcReg.isVirtual() || !DstReg.isVirtual() || 0
317 !MRI->hasOneNonDBGUse(SrcReg)) 0
318 return false; 0
319 ----
320 const TargetRegisterClass *SRC = MRI->getRegClass(SrcReg); 0
321 const TargetRegisterClass *DRC = MRI->getRegClass(DstReg); 0
322 if (SRC != DRC) 0
323 return false; 0
324 ----
325 MachineInstr *DefMI = MRI->getVRegDef(SrcReg); 0
326 if (DefMI->isCopyLike()) 0
327 return false; 0
328 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Coalescing: " << *DefMI); 0
329 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "*** to: " << MI); 0
330 MRI->replaceRegWith(DstReg, SrcReg); 0
331 MI.eraseFromParent(); 0
332 ----
333 // Conservatively, clear any kill flags, since it's possible that they are no ----
334 // longer correct. ----
335 MRI->clearKillFlags(SrcReg); 0
336 ----
337 ++NumCoalesces; 0
338 return true; 0
339 } ----

341 /// AllUsesDominatedByBlock - Return true if all uses of the specified register ----
342 /// occur in blocks dominated by the specified block. If any use is in the ----
343 /// definition block, then return false since it is never legal to move def ----
344 /// after uses. ----
345 bool MachineSinking::AllUsesDominatedByBlock(Register Reg, 0
346 MachineBasicBlock *MBB, ----
347 MachineBasicBlock *DefMBB, ----
348 bool &BreakPHIEdge, ----
349 bool &LocalUse) const { ----
350 assert(Reg.isVirtual() && "Only makes sense for vregs"); 0
351 ----
352 // Ignore debug uses because debug info doesn't affect the code. ----
353 if (MRI->use_nodbg_empty(Reg)) 0
354 return true; 0
355 ----
356 // BreakPHIEdge is true if all the uses are in the successor MBB being sunken ----
357 // into and they are all PHI nodes. In this case, machine-sink must break ----
358 // the critical edge first. e.g. ----
359 // ----
360 // %bb.1: ----
361 // Predecessors according to CFG: %bb.0 ----
362 // ... ----
363 // %def = DEC64_32r %x, implicit-def dead %eflags ----
364 // ... ----
365 // JE_4 <%bb.37>, implicit %eflags ----
366 // Successors according to CFG: %bb.37 %bb.2 ----
367 // ----
368 // %bb.2: ----
369 // %p = PHI %y, %bb.0, %def, %bb.1 ----
370 if (all_of(MRI->use_nodbg_operands(Reg), [&](MachineOperand &MO) { 0
371 MachineInstr *UseInst = MO.getParent(); 0
372 unsigned OpNo = MO.getOperandNo(); 0
373 MachineBasicBlock *UseBlock = UseInst->getParent(); 0
374 return UseBlock == MBB && UseInst->isPHI() && 0
375 UseInst->getOperand(OpNo + 1).getMBB() == DefMBB; 0
376 })) { ----
377 BreakPHIEdge = true; 0
378 return true; 0
379 } ----
380 ----
381 for (MachineOperand &MO : MRI->use_nodbg_operands(Reg)) { 0
382 // Determine the block of the use. ----
383 MachineInstr *UseInst = MO.getParent(); 0
384 unsigned OpNo = &MO - &UseInst->getOperand(0); 0
385 MachineBasicBlock *UseBlock = UseInst->getParent(); 0
386 if (UseInst->isPHI()) { 0
387 // PHI nodes use the operand in the predecessor block, not the block with ----
388 // the PHI. ----
389 UseBlock = UseInst->getOperand(OpNo+1).getMBB(); 0
390 } else if (UseBlock == DefMBB) { 0
391 LocalUse = true; 0
392 return false; 0
393 } ----
394 ----
395 // Check that it dominates. ----
396 if (!DT->dominates(MBB, UseBlock)) 0
397 return false; 0
398 } ----
399 ----
400 return true; 0
401 } ----

403 /// Return true if this machine instruction loads from global offset table or ----
404 /// constant pool. ----
405 static bool mayLoadFromGOTOrConstantPool(MachineInstr &MI) { 0
406 assert(MI.mayLoad() && "Expected MI that loads!"); 0
407 ----
408 // If we lost memory operands, conservatively assume that the instruction ----
409 // reads from everything.. ----
410 if (MI.memoperands_empty()) 0
411 return true; 0
412 ----
413 for (MachineMemOperand *MemOp : MI.memoperands()) 0
414 if (const PseudoSourceValue *PSV = MemOp->getPseudoValue()) 0
415 if (PSV->isGOT() || PSV->isConstantPool()) 0
416 return true; 0
417 ----
418 return false; 0
419 } ----

421 void MachineSinking::FindCycleSinkCandidates( 0
422 MachineCycle *Cycle, MachineBasicBlock *BB, ----
423 SmallVectorImpl &Candidates) { ----
424 for (auto &MI : *BB) { 0
425 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "CycleSink: Analysing candidate: " << MI); 0
426 if (!TII->shouldSink(MI)) { 0
427 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "CycleSink: Instruction not a candidate for this " 0
428 "target\n"); ----
429 continue; 0
430 } ----
431 if (!isCycleInvariant(Cycle, MI)) { 0
432 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "CycleSink: Instruction is not cycle invariant\n"); 0
433 continue; 0
434 } ----
435 bool DontMoveAcrossStore = true; 0
436 if (!MI.isSafeToMove(AA, DontMoveAcrossStore)) { 0
437 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "CycleSink: Instruction not safe to move.\n"); 0
438 continue; 0
439 } ----
440 if (MI.mayLoad() && !mayLoadFromGOTOrConstantPool(MI)) { 0
441 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "CycleSink: Dont sink GOT or constant pool loads\n"); 0
442 continue; 0
443 } ----
444 if (MI.isConvergent()) 0
445 continue; 0
446 ----
447 const MachineOperand &MO = MI.getOperand(0); 0
448 if (!MO.isReg() || !MO.getReg() || !MO.isDef()) 0
449 continue; 0
450 if (!MRI->hasOneDef(MO.getReg())) 0
451 continue; 0
452 ----
453 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "CycleSink: Instruction added as candidate.\n"); 0
454 Candidates.push_back(&MI); 0
455 } ----
456 } 0

458 bool MachineSinking::runOnMachineFunction(MachineFunction &MF) { 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
459 if (skipFunction(MF.getFunction())) 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
460 return false; 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
461 ----
462 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "******** Machine Sinking ********\n"); 0
463 ----
464 TII = MF.getSubtarget().getInstrInfo(); 0
465 TRI = MF.getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo(); 0
466 MRI = &MF.getRegInfo(); 0
467 DT = &getAnalysis(); 0
468 PDT = &getAnalysis(); 0
469 CI = &getAnalysis().getCycleInfo(); 0
470 MBFI = UseBlockFreqInfo ? &getAnalysis() : nullptr; 0
471 MBPI = &getAnalysis(); 0
472 AA = &getAnalysis().getAAResults(); 0
473 RegClassInfo.runOnMachineFunction(MF); 0
474 ----
475 bool EverMadeChange = false; 0
476 ----
477 while (true) { ----
478 bool MadeChange = false; 0
479 ----
480 // Process all basic blocks. ----
481 CEBCandidates.clear(); 0
482 ToSplit.clear(); 0
483 for (auto &MBB: MF) 0
484 MadeChange |= ProcessBlock(MBB); 0
485 ----
486 // If we have anything we marked as toSplit, split it now. ----
487 for (const auto &Pair : ToSplit) { 0
488 auto NewSucc = Pair.first->SplitCriticalEdge(Pair.second, *this); 0
489 if (NewSucc != nullptr) { 0
490 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " *** Splitting critical edge: " 0
491 << printMBBReference(*Pair.first) << " -- " ----
492 << printMBBReference(*NewSucc) << " -- " ----
493 << printMBBReference(*Pair.second) << '\n'); ----
494 if (MBFI) 0
495 MBFI->onEdgeSplit(*Pair.first, *NewSucc, *MBPI); 0
496 ----
497 MadeChange = true; 0
498 ++NumSplit; 0
499 } else ----
500 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " *** Not legal to break critical edge\n"); 0
501 } ----
502 // If this iteration over the code changed anything, keep iterating. ----
503 if (!MadeChange) break; 0
504 EverMadeChange = true; 0
505 } 0
506 ----
507 if (SinkInstsIntoCycle) { 0
508 SmallVector Cycles(CI->toplevel_begin(), 0
509 CI->toplevel_end()); 0
510 for (auto *Cycle : Cycles) { 0
511 MachineBasicBlock *Preheader = Cycle->getCyclePreheader(); 0
512 if (!Preheader) { 0
513 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "CycleSink: Can't find preheader\n"); 0
514 continue; 0
515 } ----
516 SmallVector Candidates; 0
517 FindCycleSinkCandidates(Cycle, Preheader, Candidates); 0
518 ----
519 // Walk the candidates in reverse order so that we start with the use ----
520 // of a def-use chain, if there is any. ----
521 // TODO: Sort the candidates using a cost-model. ----
522 unsigned i = 0; 0
523 for (MachineInstr *I : llvm::reverse(Candidates)) { 0
524 if (i++ == SinkIntoCycleLimit) { 0
525 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "CycleSink: Limit reached of instructions to " 0
526 "be analysed."); ----
527 break; 0
528 } ----
529 ----
530 if (!SinkIntoCycle(Cycle, *I)) 0
531 break; 0
532 EverMadeChange = true; 0
533 ++NumCycleSunk; 0
534 } ----
535 } 0
536 } 0
537 ----
538 HasStoreCache.clear(); 0
539 StoreInstrCache.clear(); 0
540 ----
541 // Now clear any kill flags for recorded registers. ----
542 for (auto I : RegsToClearKillFlags) 0
543 MRI->clearKillFlags(I); 0
544 RegsToClearKillFlags.clear(); 0
545 ----
546 return EverMadeChange; 0
547 } ----

549 bool MachineSinking::ProcessBlock(MachineBasicBlock &MBB) { 0
550 // Can't sink anything out of a block that has less than two successors. ----
551 if (MBB.succ_size() <= 1 || MBB.empty()) return false; 0
552 ----
553 // Don't bother sinking code out of unreachable blocks. In addition to being ----
554 // unprofitable, it can also lead to infinite looping, because in an ----
555 // unreachable cycle there may be nowhere to stop. ----
556 if (!DT->isReachableFromEntry(&MBB)) return false; 0
557 ----
558 bool MadeChange = false; 0
559 ----
560 // Cache all successors, sorted by frequency info and cycle depth. ----
561 AllSuccsCache AllSuccessors; 0
562 ----
563 // Walk the basic block bottom-up. Remember if we saw a store. ----
564 MachineBasicBlock::iterator I = MBB.end(); 0
565 --I; 0
566 bool ProcessedBegin, SawStore = false; 0
567 do { ----
568 MachineInstr &MI = *I; // The instruction to sink. 0
569 ----
570 // Predecrement I (if it's not begin) so that it isn't invalidated by ----
571 // sinking. ----
572 ProcessedBegin = I == MBB.begin(); 0
573 if (!ProcessedBegin) 0
574 --I; 0
575 ----
576 if (MI.isDebugOrPseudoInstr()) { 0
577 if (MI.isDebugValue()) 0
578 ProcessDbgInst(MI); 0
579 continue; 0
580 } ----
581 ----
582 bool Joined = PerformTrivialForwardCoalescing(MI, &MBB); 0
583 if (Joined) { 0
584 MadeChange = true; 0
585 continue; 0
586 } ----
587 ----
588 if (SinkInstruction(MI, SawStore, AllSuccessors)) { 0
589 ++NumSunk; 0
590 MadeChange = true; 0
591 } ----
592 ----
593 // If we just processed the first instruction in the block, we're done. ----
594 } while (!ProcessedBegin); 0
595 ----
596 SeenDbgUsers.clear(); 0
597 SeenDbgVars.clear(); 0
598 // recalculate the bb register pressure after sinking one BB. ----
599 CachedRegisterPressure.clear(); 0
600 ----
601 return MadeChange; 0
602 } 0
603 ----
604 void MachineSinking::ProcessDbgInst(MachineInstr &MI) { 0
605 // When we see DBG_VALUEs for registers, record any vreg it reads, so that ----
606 // we know what to sink if the vreg def sinks. ----
607 assert(MI.isDebugValue() && "Expected DBG_VALUE for processing"); 0
608 ----
609 DebugVariable Var(MI.getDebugVariable(), MI.getDebugExpression(), ----
610 MI.getDebugLoc()->getInlinedAt()); 0
611 bool SeenBefore = SeenDbgVars.contains(Var); 0
612 ----
613 for (MachineOperand &MO : MI.debug_operands()) { 0
614 if (MO.isReg() && MO.getReg().isVirtual()) 0
615 SeenDbgUsers[MO.getReg()].push_back(SeenDbgUser(&MI, SeenBefore)); 0
616 } ----
617 ----
618 // Record the variable for any DBG_VALUE, to avoid re-ordering any of them. ----
619 SeenDbgVars.insert(Var); 0
620 } 0
621 ----
622 bool MachineSinking::isWorthBreakingCriticalEdge(MachineInstr &MI, 0
623 MachineBasicBlock *From, ----
624 MachineBasicBlock *To) { ----
625 // FIXME: Need much better heuristics. ----
626 ----
627 // If the pass has already considered breaking this edge (during this pass ----
628 // through the function), then let's go ahead and break it. This means ----
629 // sinking multiple "cheap" instructions into the same block. ----
630 if (!CEBCandidates.insert(std::make_pair(From, To)).second) 0
631 return true; 0
632 ----
633 if (!MI.isCopy() && !TII->isAsCheapAsAMove(MI)) 0
634 return true; 0
635 ----
636 if (From->isSuccessor(To) && MBPI->getEdgeProbability(From, To) <= 0
637 BranchProbability(SplitEdgeProbabilityThreshold, 100)) ----
638 return true; 0
639 ----
640 // MI is cheap, we probably don't want to break the critical edge for it. ----
641 // However, if this would allow some definitions of its source operands ----
642 // to be sunk then it's probably worth it. ----
643 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI.all_uses()) { 0
644 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
645 if (Reg == 0) 0
646 continue; 0
647 ----
648 // We don't move live definitions of physical registers, ----
649 // so sinking their uses won't enable any opportunities. ----
650 if (Reg.isPhysical()) 0
651 continue; 0
652 ----
653 // If this instruction is the only user of a virtual register, ----
654 // check if breaking the edge will enable sinking ----
655 // both this instruction and the defining instruction. ----
656 if (MRI->hasOneNonDBGUse(Reg)) { 0
657 // If the definition resides in same MBB, ----
658 // claim it's likely we can sink these together. ----
659 // If definition resides elsewhere, we aren't ----
660 // blocking it from being sunk so don't break the edge. ----
661 MachineInstr *DefMI = MRI->getVRegDef(Reg); 0
662 if (DefMI->getParent() == MI.getParent()) 0
663 return true; 0
664 } ----
665 } ----
666 ----
667 return false; 0
668 } ----
669 ----
670 bool MachineSinking::PostponeSplitCriticalEdge(MachineInstr &MI, 0
671 MachineBasicBlock *FromBB, ----
672 MachineBasicBlock *ToBB, ----
673 bool BreakPHIEdge) { ----
674 if (!isWorthBreakingCriticalEdge(MI, FromBB, ToBB)) 0
675 return false; 0
676 ----
677 // Avoid breaking back edge. From == To means backedge for single BB cycle. ----
678 if (!SplitEdges || FromBB == ToBB) 0
679 return false; 0
680 ----
681 MachineCycle *FromCycle = CI->getCycle(FromBB); 0
682 MachineCycle *ToCycle = CI->getCycle(ToBB); 0
683 ----
684 // Check for backedges of more "complex" cycles. ----
685 if (FromCycle == ToCycle && FromCycle && 0
686 (!FromCycle->isReducible() || FromCycle->getHeader() == ToBB)) 0
687 return false; 0
688 ----
689 // It's not always legal to break critical edges and sink the computation ----
690 // to the edge. ----
691 // ----
692 // %bb.1: ----
693 // v1024 ----
694 // Beq %bb.3 ----
695 // ----
696 // %bb.2: ----
697 // ... no uses of v1024 ----
698 // ----
699 // %bb.3: ----
700 // ... ----
701 // = v1024 ----
702 // ----
703 // If %bb.1 -> %bb.3 edge is broken and computation of v1024 is inserted: ----
704 // ----
705 // %bb.1: ----
706 // ... ----
707 // Bne %bb.2 ----
708 // %bb.4: ----
709 // v1024 = ----
710 // B %bb.3 ----
711 // %bb.2: ----
712 // ... no uses of v1024 ----
713 // ----
714 // %bb.3: ----
715 // ... ----
716 // = v1024 ----
717 // ----
718 // This is incorrect since v1024 is not computed along the %bb.1->%bb.2->%bb.3 ----
719 // flow. We need to ensure the new basic block where the computation is ----
720 // sunk to dominates all the uses. ----
721 // It's only legal to break critical edge and sink the computation to the ----
722 // new block if all the predecessors of "To", except for "From", are ----
723 // not dominated by "From". Given SSA property, this means these ----
724 // predecessors are dominated by "To". ----
725 // ----
726 // There is no need to do this check if all the uses are PHI nodes. PHI ----
727 // sources are only defined on the specific predecessor edges. ----
728 if (!BreakPHIEdge) { 0
729 for (MachineBasicBlock *Pred : ToBB->predecessors()) 0
730 if (Pred != FromBB && !DT->dominates(ToBB, Pred)) 0
731 return false; 0
732 } ----
733 ----
734 ToSplit.insert(std::make_pair(FromBB, ToBB)); 0
735 ----
736 return true; 0
737 } ----
738 ----
739 std::vector & ----
740 MachineSinking::getBBRegisterPressure(MachineBasicBlock &MBB) { 0
741 // Currently to save compiling time, MBB's register pressure will not change ----
742 // in one ProcessBlock iteration because of CachedRegisterPressure. but MBB's ----
743 // register pressure is changed after sinking any instructions into it. ----
744 // FIXME: need a accurate and cheap register pressure estiminate model here. ----
745 auto RP = CachedRegisterPressure.find(&MBB); 0
746 if (RP != CachedRegisterPressure.end()) 0
747 return RP->second; 0
748 ----
749 RegionPressure Pressure; 0
750 RegPressureTracker RPTracker(Pressure); 0
751 ----
752 // Initialize the register pressure tracker. ----
753 RPTracker.init(MBB.getParent(), &RegClassInfo, nullptr, &MBB, MBB.end(), 0
754 /*TrackLaneMasks*/ false, /*TrackUntiedDefs=*/true); ----
755 ----
756 for (MachineBasicBlock::iterator MII = MBB.instr_end(), 0
757 MIE = MBB.instr_begin(); 0
758 MII != MIE; --MII) { 0
759 MachineInstr &MI = *std::prev(MII); 0
760 if (MI.isDebugInstr() || MI.isPseudoProbe()) 0
761 continue; 0
762 RegisterOperands RegOpers; 0
763 RegOpers.collect(MI, *TRI, *MRI, false, false); 0
764 RPTracker.recedeSkipDebugValues(); 0
765 assert(&*RPTracker.getPos() == &MI && "RPTracker sync error!"); 0
766 RPTracker.recede(RegOpers); 0
767 } 0
768 ----
769 RPTracker.closeRegion(); 0
770 auto It = CachedRegisterPressure.insert( 0
771 std::make_pair(&MBB, RPTracker.getPressure().MaxSetPressure)); 0
772 return It.first->second; 0
773 } 0
774 ----
775 /// isProfitableToSinkTo - Return true if it is profitable to sink MI. ----
776 bool MachineSinking::isProfitableToSinkTo(Register Reg, MachineInstr &MI, 0
777 MachineBasicBlock *MBB, ----
778 MachineBasicBlock *SuccToSinkTo, ----
779 AllSuccsCache &AllSuccessors) { ----
780 assert (SuccToSinkTo && "Invalid SinkTo Candidate BB"); 0
781 ----
782 if (MBB == SuccToSinkTo) 0
783 return false; 0
784 ----
785 // It is profitable if SuccToSinkTo does not post dominate current block. ----
786 if (!PDT->dominates(SuccToSinkTo, MBB)) 0
787 return true; 0
788 ----
789 // It is profitable to sink an instruction from a deeper cycle to a shallower ----
790 // cycle, even if the latter post-dominates the former (PR21115). ----
791 if (CI->getCycleDepth(MBB) > CI->getCycleDepth(SuccToSinkTo)) 0
792 return true; 0
793 ----
794 // Check if only use in post dominated block is PHI instruction. ----
795 bool NonPHIUse = false; 0
796 for (MachineInstr &UseInst : MRI->use_nodbg_instructions(Reg)) { 0
797 MachineBasicBlock *UseBlock = UseInst.getParent(); 0
798 if (UseBlock == SuccToSinkTo && !UseInst.isPHI()) 0
799 NonPHIUse = true; 0
800 } ----
801 if (!NonPHIUse) 0
802 return true; 0
803 ----
804 // If SuccToSinkTo post dominates then also it may be profitable if MI ----
805 // can further profitably sinked into another block in next round. ----
806 bool BreakPHIEdge = false; 0
807 // FIXME - If finding successor is compile time expensive then cache results. ----
808 if (MachineBasicBlock *MBB2 = 0
809 FindSuccToSinkTo(MI, SuccToSinkTo, BreakPHIEdge, AllSuccessors)) 0
810 return isProfitableToSinkTo(Reg, MI, SuccToSinkTo, MBB2, AllSuccessors); 0
811 ----
812 MachineCycle *MCycle = CI->getCycle(MBB); 0
813 ----
814 // If the instruction is not inside a cycle, it is not profitable to sink MI to ----
815 // a post dominate block SuccToSinkTo. ----
816 if (!MCycle) 0
817 return false; 0
818 ----
819 auto isRegisterPressureSetExceedLimit = [&](const TargetRegisterClass *RC) { 0
820 unsigned Weight = TRI->getRegClassWeight(RC).RegWeight; 0
821 const int *PS = TRI->getRegClassPressureSets(RC); 0
822 // Get register pressure for block SuccToSinkTo. ----
823 std::vector BBRegisterPressure = ----
824 getBBRegisterPressure(*SuccToSinkTo); 0
825 for (; *PS != -1; PS++) 0
826 // check if any register pressure set exceeds limit in block SuccToSinkTo ----
827 // after sinking. ----
828 if (Weight + BBRegisterPressure[*PS] >= 0
829 TRI->getRegPressureSetLimit(*MBB->getParent(), *PS)) 0
830 return true; 0
831 return false; 0
832 }; 0
833 ----
834 // If this instruction is inside a Cycle and sinking this instruction can make ----
835 // more registers live range shorten, it is still prifitable. ----
836 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI.operands()) { 0
837 // Ignore non-register operands. ----
838 if (!MO.isReg()) 0
839 continue; 0
840 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
841 if (Reg == 0) 0
842 continue; 0
843 ----
844 if (Reg.isPhysical()) { 0
845 // Don't handle non-constant and non-ignorable physical register uses. ----
846 if (MO.isUse() && !MRI->isConstantPhysReg(Reg) && !TII->isIgnorableUse(MO)) 0
847 return false; 0
848 continue; 0
849 } ----
850 ----
851 // Users for the defs are all dominated by SuccToSinkTo. ----
852 if (MO.isDef()) { 0
853 // This def register's live range is shortened after sinking. ----
854 bool LocalUse = false; 0
855 if (!AllUsesDominatedByBlock(Reg, SuccToSinkTo, MBB, BreakPHIEdge, 0
856 LocalUse)) ----
857 return false; 0
858 } else { ----
859 MachineInstr *DefMI = MRI->getVRegDef(Reg); 0
860 if (!DefMI) 0
861 continue; 0
862 MachineCycle *Cycle = CI->getCycle(DefMI->getParent()); 0
863 // DefMI is defined outside of cycle. There should be no live range ----
864 // impact for this operand. Defination outside of cycle means: ----
865 // 1: defination is outside of cycle. ----
866 // 2: defination is in this cycle, but it is a PHI in the cycle header. ----
867 if (Cycle != MCycle || (DefMI->isPHI() && Cycle && Cycle->isReducible() && 0
868 Cycle->getHeader() == DefMI->getParent())) 0
869 continue; 0
870 // The DefMI is defined inside the cycle. ----
871 // If sinking this operand makes some register pressure set exceed limit, ----
872 // it is not profitable. ----
873 if (isRegisterPressureSetExceedLimit(MRI->getRegClass(Reg))) { 0
874 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "register pressure exceed limit, not profitable."); 0
875 return false; 0
876 } ----
877 } ----
878 } ----
879 ----
880 // If MI is in cycle and all its operands are alive across the whole cycle or ----
881 // if no operand sinking make register pressure set exceed limit, it is ----
882 // profitable to sink MI. ----
883 return true; 0
884 } ----
885 ----
886 /// Get the sorted sequence of successors for this MachineBasicBlock, possibly ----
887 /// computing it if it was not already cached. ----
888 SmallVector & ----
889 MachineSinking::GetAllSortedSuccessors(MachineInstr &MI, MachineBasicBlock *MBB, 0
890 AllSuccsCache &AllSuccessors) const { ----
891 // Do we have the sorted successors in cache ? ----
892 auto Succs = AllSuccessors.find(MBB); 0
893 if (Succs != AllSuccessors.end()) 0
894 return Succs->second; 0
895 ----
896 SmallVector AllSuccs(MBB->successors()); 0
897 ----
898 // Handle cases where sinking can happen but where the sink point isn't a ----
899 // successor. For example: ----
900 // ----
901 // x = computation ----
902 // if () {} else {} ----
903 // use x ----
904 // ----
905 for (MachineDomTreeNode *DTChild : DT->getNode(MBB)->children()) { 0
906 // DomTree children of MBB that have MBB as immediate dominator are added. ----
907 if (DTChild->getIDom()->getBlock() == MI.getParent() && 0
908 // Skip MBBs already added to the AllSuccs vector above. ----
909 !MBB->isSuccessor(DTChild->getBlock())) 0
910 AllSuccs.push_back(DTChild->getBlock()); 0
911 } ----
912 ----
913 // Sort Successors according to their cycle depth or block frequency info. ----
914 llvm::stable_sort( 0
915 AllSuccs, [this](const MachineBasicBlock *L, const MachineBasicBlock *R) { 0
916 uint64_t LHSFreq = MBFI ? MBFI->getBlockFreq(L).getFrequency() : 0; 0
917 uint64_t RHSFreq = MBFI ? MBFI->getBlockFreq(R).getFrequency() : 0; 0
918 bool HasBlockFreq = LHSFreq != 0 && RHSFreq != 0; 0
919 return HasBlockFreq ? LHSFreq < RHSFreq 0
920 : CI->getCycleDepth(L) < CI->getCycleDepth(R); 0
921 }); ----
922 ----
923 auto it = AllSuccessors.insert(std::make_pair(MBB, AllSuccs)); 0
924 ----
925 return it.first->second; 0
926 } 0
927 ----
928 /// FindSuccToSinkTo - Find a successor to sink this instruction to. ----
929 MachineBasicBlock * ----
930 MachineSinking::FindSuccToSinkTo(MachineInstr &MI, MachineBasicBlock *MBB, 0
931 bool &BreakPHIEdge, ----
932 AllSuccsCache &AllSuccessors) { ----
933 assert (MBB && "Invalid MachineBasicBlock!"); 0
934 ----
935 // loop over all the operands of the specified instruction. If there is ----
936 // anything we can't handle, bail out. ----
937 ----
938 // SuccToSinkTo - This is the successor to sink this instruction to, once we ----
939 // decide. ----
940 MachineBasicBlock *SuccToSinkTo = nullptr; 0
941 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI.operands()) { 0
942 if (!MO.isReg()) continue; // Ignore non-register operands. 0
943 ----
944 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
945 if (Reg == 0) continue; 0
946 ----
947 if (Reg.isPhysical()) { 0
948 if (MO.isUse()) { 0
949 // If the physreg has no defs anywhere, it's just an ambient register ----
950 // and we can freely move its uses. Alternatively, if it's allocatable, ----
951 // it could get allocated to something with a def during allocation. ----
952 if (!MRI->isConstantPhysReg(Reg) && !TII->isIgnorableUse(MO)) 0
953 return nullptr; 0
954 } else if (!MO.isDead()) { 0
955 // A def that isn't dead. We can't move it. ----
956 return nullptr; 0
957 } ----
958 } else { ----
959 // Virtual register uses are always safe to sink. ----
960 if (MO.isUse()) continue; 0
961 ----
962 // If it's not safe to move defs of the register class, then abort. ----
963 if (!TII->isSafeToMoveRegClassDefs(MRI->getRegClass(Reg))) 0
964 return nullptr; 0
965 ----
966 // Virtual register defs can only be sunk if all their uses are in blocks ----
967 // dominated by one of the successors. ----
968 if (SuccToSinkTo) { 0
969 // If a previous operand picked a block to sink to, then this operand ----
970 // must be sinkable to the same block. ----
971 bool LocalUse = false; 0
972 if (!AllUsesDominatedByBlock(Reg, SuccToSinkTo, MBB, 0
973 BreakPHIEdge, LocalUse)) ----
974 return nullptr; 0
975 ----
976 continue; 0
977 } 0
978 ----
979 // Otherwise, we should look at all the successors and decide which one ----
980 // we should sink to. If we have reliable block frequency information ----
981 // (frequency != 0) available, give successors with smaller frequencies ----
982 // higher priority, otherwise prioritize smaller cycle depths. ----
983 for (MachineBasicBlock *SuccBlock : 0
984 GetAllSortedSuccessors(MI, MBB, AllSuccessors)) { 0
985 bool LocalUse = false; 0
986 if (AllUsesDominatedByBlock(Reg, SuccBlock, MBB, 0
987 BreakPHIEdge, LocalUse)) { ----
988 SuccToSinkTo = SuccBlock; 0
989 break; 0
990 } ----
991 if (LocalUse) 0
992 // Def is used locally, it's never safe to move this def. ----
993 return nullptr; 0
994 } ----
995 ----
996 // If we couldn't find a block to sink to, ignore this instruction. ----
997 if (!SuccToSinkTo) 0
998 return nullptr; 0
999 if (!isProfitableToSinkTo(Reg, MI, MBB, SuccToSinkTo, AllSuccessors)) 0
1000 return nullptr; 0
1001 } ----
1002 } ----
1003 ----
1004 // It is not possible to sink an instruction into its own block. This can ----
1005 // happen with cycles. ----
1006 if (MBB == SuccToSinkTo) 0
1007 return nullptr; 0
1008 ----
1009 if (!SuccToSinkTo) 0
1010 return nullptr; 0
1011 ----
1012 // It's not safe to sink instructions to EH landing pad. Control flow into ----
1013 // landing pad is implicitly defined. ----
1014 if (SuccToSinkTo->isEHPad()) 0
1015 return nullptr; 0
1016 ----
1017 // It ought to be okay to sink instructions into an INLINEASM_BR target, but ----
1018 // only if we make sure that MI occurs _before_ an INLINEASM_BR instruction in ----
1019 // the source block (which this code does not yet do). So for now, forbid ----
1020 // doing so. ----
1021 if (SuccToSinkTo->isInlineAsmBrIndirectTarget()) 0
1022 return nullptr; 0
1023 ----
1024 MachineBasicBlock::const_iterator InsertPos = ----
1025 SuccToSinkTo->SkipPHIsAndLabels(SuccToSinkTo->begin()); 0
1026 if (blockPrologueInterferes(SuccToSinkTo, InsertPos, MI, TRI, TII, MRI)) 0
1027 return nullptr; 0
1028 ----
1029 return SuccToSinkTo; 0
1030 } ----
1031 ----
1032 /// Return true if MI is likely to be usable as a memory operation by the ----
1033 /// implicit null check optimization. ----
1034 /// ----
1035 /// This is a "best effort" heuristic, and should not be relied upon for ----
1036 /// correctness. This returning true does not guarantee that the implicit null ----
1037 /// check optimization is legal over MI, and this returning false does not ----
1038 /// guarantee MI cannot possibly be used to do a null check. ----
1039 static bool SinkingPreventsImplicitNullCheck(MachineInstr &MI, 0
1040 const TargetInstrInfo *TII, ----
1041 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI) { ----
1042 using MachineBranchPredicate = TargetInstrInfo::MachineBranchPredicate; ----
1043 ----
1044 auto *MBB = MI.getParent(); 0
1045 if (MBB->pred_size() != 1) 0
1046 return false; 0
1047 ----
1048 auto *PredMBB = *MBB->pred_begin(); 0
1049 auto *PredBB = PredMBB->getBasicBlock(); 0
1050 ----
1051 // Frontends that don't use implicit null checks have no reason to emit ----
1052 // branches with make.implicit metadata, and this function should always ----
1053 // return false for them. ----
1054 if (!PredBB || 0
1055 !PredBB->getTerminator()->getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_make_implicit)) 0
1056 return false; 0
1057 ----
1058 const MachineOperand *BaseOp; ----
1059 int64_t Offset; ----
1060 bool OffsetIsScalable; ----
1061 if (!TII->getMemOperandWithOffset(MI, BaseOp, Offset, OffsetIsScalable, TRI)) 0
1062 return false; 0
1063 ----
1064 if (!BaseOp->isReg()) 0
1065 return false; 0
1066 ----
1067 if (!(MI.mayLoad() && !MI.isPredicable())) 0
1068 return false; 0
1069 ----
1070 MachineBranchPredicate MBP; 0
1071 if (TII->analyzeBranchPredicate(*PredMBB, MBP, false)) 0
1072 return false; 0
1073 ----
1074 return MBP.LHS.isReg() && MBP.RHS.isImm() && MBP.RHS.getImm() == 0 && 0
1075 (MBP.Predicate == MachineBranchPredicate::PRED_NE || 0
1076 MBP.Predicate == MachineBranchPredicate::PRED_EQ) && 0
1077 MBP.LHS.getReg() == BaseOp->getReg(); 0
1078 } ----
1079 ----
1080 /// If the sunk instruction is a copy, try to forward the copy instead of ----
1081 /// leaving an 'undef' DBG_VALUE in the original location. Don't do this if ----
1082 /// there's any subregister weirdness involved. Returns true if copy ----
1083 /// propagation occurred. ----
1084 static bool attemptDebugCopyProp(MachineInstr &SinkInst, MachineInstr &DbgMI, 0
1085 Register Reg) { ----
1086 const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = SinkInst.getMF()->getRegInfo(); 0
1087 const TargetInstrInfo &TII = *SinkInst.getMF()->getSubtarget().getInstrInfo(); 0
1088 ----
1089 // Copy DBG_VALUE operand and set the original to undef. We then check to ----
1090 // see whether this is something that can be copy-forwarded. If it isn't, ----
1091 // continue around the loop. ----
1092 ----
1093 const MachineOperand *SrcMO = nullptr, *DstMO = nullptr; 0
1094 auto CopyOperands = TII.isCopyInstr(SinkInst); 0
1095 if (!CopyOperands) 0
1096 return false; 0
1097 SrcMO = CopyOperands->Source; 0
1098 DstMO = CopyOperands->Destination; 0
1099 ----
1100 // Check validity of forwarding this copy. ----
1101 bool PostRA = MRI.getNumVirtRegs() == 0; 0
1102 ----
1103 // Trying to forward between physical and virtual registers is too hard. ----
1104 if (Reg.isVirtual() != SrcMO->getReg().isVirtual()) 0
1105 return false; 0
1106 ----
1107 // Only try virtual register copy-forwarding before regalloc, and physical ----
1108 // register copy-forwarding after regalloc. ----
1109 bool arePhysRegs = !Reg.isVirtual(); 0
1110 if (arePhysRegs != PostRA) 0
1111 return false; 0
1112 ----
1113 // Pre-regalloc, only forward if all subregisters agree (or there are no ----
1114 // subregs at all). More analysis might recover some forwardable copies. ----
1115 if (!PostRA) 0
1116 for (auto &DbgMO : DbgMI.getDebugOperandsForReg(Reg)) 0
1117 if (DbgMO.getSubReg() != SrcMO->getSubReg() || 0
1118 DbgMO.getSubReg() != DstMO->getSubReg()) 0
1119 return false; 0
1120 ----
1121 // Post-regalloc, we may be sinking a DBG_VALUE of a sub or super-register ----
1122 // of this copy. Only forward the copy if the DBG_VALUE operand exactly ----
1123 // matches the copy destination. ----
1124 if (PostRA && Reg != DstMO->getReg()) 0
1125 return false; 0
1126 ----
1127 for (auto &DbgMO : DbgMI.getDebugOperandsForReg(Reg)) { 0
1128 DbgMO.setReg(SrcMO->getReg()); 0
1129 DbgMO.setSubReg(SrcMO->getSubReg()); 0
1130 } 0
1131 return true; 0
1132 } ----
1133 ----
1134 using MIRegs = std::pair>; ----
1135 /// Sink an instruction and its associated debug instructions. ----
1136 static void performSink(MachineInstr &MI, MachineBasicBlock &SuccToSinkTo, 0
1137 MachineBasicBlock::iterator InsertPos, ----
1138 ArrayRef DbgValuesToSink) { ----
1139 // If we cannot find a location to use (merge with), then we erase the debug ----
1140 // location to prevent debug-info driven tools from potentially reporting ----
1141 // wrong location information. ----
1142 if (!SuccToSinkTo.empty() && InsertPos != SuccToSinkTo.end()) 0
1143 MI.setDebugLoc(DILocation::getMergedLocation(MI.getDebugLoc(), 0
1144 InsertPos->getDebugLoc())); 0
1145 else ----
1146 MI.setDebugLoc(DebugLoc()); 0
1147 ----
1148 // Move the instruction. ----
1149 MachineBasicBlock *ParentBlock = MI.getParent(); 0
1150 SuccToSinkTo.splice(InsertPos, ParentBlock, MI, 0
1151 ++MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI)); 0
1152 ----
1153 // Sink a copy of debug users to the insert position. Mark the original ----
1154 // DBG_VALUE location as 'undef', indicating that any earlier variable ----
1155 // location should be terminated as we've optimised away the value at this ----
1156 // point. ----
1157 for (const auto &DbgValueToSink : DbgValuesToSink) { 0
1158 MachineInstr *DbgMI = DbgValueToSink.first; 0
1159 MachineInstr *NewDbgMI = DbgMI->getMF()->CloneMachineInstr(DbgMI); 0
1160 SuccToSinkTo.insert(InsertPos, NewDbgMI); 0
1161 ----
1162 bool PropagatedAllSunkOps = true; 0
1163 for (unsigned Reg : DbgValueToSink.second) { 0
1164 if (DbgMI->hasDebugOperandForReg(Reg)) { 0
1165 if (!attemptDebugCopyProp(MI, *DbgMI, Reg)) { 0
1166 PropagatedAllSunkOps = false; 0
1167 break; 0
1168 } ----
1169 } ----
1170 } ----
1171 if (!PropagatedAllSunkOps) 0
1172 DbgMI->setDebugValueUndef(); 0
1173 } ----
1174 } 0
1175 ----
1176 /// hasStoreBetween - check if there is store betweeen straight line blocks From ----
1177 /// and To. ----
1178 bool MachineSinking::hasStoreBetween(MachineBasicBlock *From, 0
1179 MachineBasicBlock *To, MachineInstr &MI) { ----
1180 // Make sure From and To are in straight line which means From dominates To ----
1181 // and To post dominates From. ----
1182 if (!DT->dominates(From, To) || !PDT->dominates(To, From)) 0
1183 return true; 0
1184 ----
1185 auto BlockPair = std::make_pair(From, To); 0
1186 ----
1187 // Does these two blocks pair be queried before and have a definite cached ----
1188 // result? ----
1189 if (HasStoreCache.find(BlockPair) != HasStoreCache.end()) 0
1190 return HasStoreCache[BlockPair]; 0
1191 ----
1192 if (StoreInstrCache.find(BlockPair) != StoreInstrCache.end()) 0
1193 return llvm::any_of(StoreInstrCache[BlockPair], [&](MachineInstr *I) { 0
1194 return I->mayAlias(AA, MI, false); 0
1195 }); 0
1196 ----
1197 bool SawStore = false; 0
1198 bool HasAliasedStore = false; 0
1199 DenseSet HandledBlocks; 0
1200 DenseSet HandledDomBlocks; 0
1201 // Go through all reachable blocks from From. ----
1202 for (MachineBasicBlock *BB : depth_first(From)) { 0
1203 // We insert the instruction at the start of block To, so no need to worry ----
1204 // about stores inside To. ----
1205 // Store in block From should be already considered when just enter function ----
1206 // SinkInstruction. ----
1207 if (BB == To || BB == From) 0
1208 continue; 0
1209 ----
1210 // We already handle this BB in previous iteration. ----
1211 if (HandledBlocks.count(BB)) 0
1212 continue; 0
1213 ----
1214 HandledBlocks.insert(BB); 0
1215 // To post dominates BB, it must be a path from block From. ----
1216 if (PDT->dominates(To, BB)) { 0
1217 if (!HandledDomBlocks.count(BB)) 0
1218 HandledDomBlocks.insert(BB); 0
1219 ----
1220 // If this BB is too big or the block number in straight line between From ----
1221 // and To is too big, stop searching to save compiling time. ----
1222 if (BB->sizeWithoutDebugLargerThan(SinkLoadInstsPerBlockThreshold) || 0
1223 HandledDomBlocks.size() > SinkLoadBlocksThreshold) { 0
1224 for (auto *DomBB : HandledDomBlocks) { 0
1225 if (DomBB != BB && DT->dominates(DomBB, BB)) 0
1226 HasStoreCache[std::make_pair(DomBB, To)] = true; 0
1227 else if(DomBB != BB && DT->dominates(BB, DomBB)) 0
1228 HasStoreCache[std::make_pair(From, DomBB)] = true; 0
1229 } ----
1230 HasStoreCache[BlockPair] = true; 0
1231 return true; 0
1232 } ----
1233 ----
1234 for (MachineInstr &I : *BB) { 0
1235 // Treat as alias conservatively for a call or an ordered memory ----
1236 // operation. ----
1237 if (I.isCall() || I.hasOrderedMemoryRef()) { 0
1238 for (auto *DomBB : HandledDomBlocks) { 0
1239 if (DomBB != BB && DT->dominates(DomBB, BB)) 0
1240 HasStoreCache[std::make_pair(DomBB, To)] = true; 0
1241 else if(DomBB != BB && DT->dominates(BB, DomBB)) 0
1242 HasStoreCache[std::make_pair(From, DomBB)] = true; 0
1243 } ----
1244 HasStoreCache[BlockPair] = true; 0
1245 return true; 0
1246 } ----
1247 ----
1248 if (I.mayStore()) { 0
1249 SawStore = true; 0
1250 // We still have chance to sink MI if all stores between are not ----
1251 // aliased to MI. ----
1252 // Cache all store instructions, so that we don't need to go through ----
1253 // all From reachable blocks for next load instruction. ----
1254 if (I.mayAlias(AA, MI, false)) 0
1255 HasAliasedStore = true; 0
1256 StoreInstrCache[BlockPair].push_back(&I); 0
1257 } ----
1258 } ----
1259 } ----
1260 } 0
1261 // If there is no store at all, cache the result. ----
1262 if (!SawStore) 0
1263 HasStoreCache[BlockPair] = false; 0
1264 return HasAliasedStore; 0
1265 } 0
1266 ----
1267 /// Sink instructions into cycles if profitable. This especially tries to ----
1268 /// prevent register spills caused by register pressure if there is little to no ----
1269 /// overhead moving instructions into cycles. ----
1270 bool MachineSinking::SinkIntoCycle(MachineCycle *Cycle, MachineInstr &I) { 0
1271 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "CycleSink: Finding sink block for: " << I); 0
1272 MachineBasicBlock *Preheader = Cycle->getCyclePreheader(); 0
1273 assert(Preheader && "Cycle sink needs a preheader block"); 0
1274 MachineBasicBlock *SinkBlock = nullptr; 0
1275 bool CanSink = true; 0
1276 const MachineOperand &MO = I.getOperand(0); 0
1277 ----
1278 for (MachineInstr &MI : MRI->use_instructions(MO.getReg())) { 0
1279 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "CycleSink: Analysing use: " << MI); 0
1280 if (!Cycle->contains(MI.getParent())) { 0
1281 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "CycleSink: Use not in cycle, can't sink.\n"); 0
1282 CanSink = false; 0
1283 break; 0
1284 } ----
1285 ----
1286 // FIXME: Come up with a proper cost model that estimates whether sinking ----
1287 // the instruction (and thus possibly executing it on every cycle ----
1288 // iteration) is more expensive than a register. ----
1289 // For now assumes that copies are cheap and thus almost always worth it. ----
1290 if (!MI.isCopy()) { 0
1291 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "CycleSink: Use is not a copy\n"); 0
1292 CanSink = false; 0
1293 break; 0
1294 } ----
1295 if (!SinkBlock) { 0
1296 SinkBlock = MI.getParent(); 0
1297 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "CycleSink: Setting sink block to: " 0
1298 << printMBBReference(*SinkBlock) << "\n"); ----
1299 continue; 0
1300 } ----
1301 SinkBlock = DT->findNearestCommonDominator(SinkBlock, MI.getParent()); 0
1302 if (!SinkBlock) { 0
1303 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "CycleSink: Can't find nearest dominator\n"); 0
1304 CanSink = false; 0
1305 break; 0
1306 } ----
1307 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "CycleSink: Setting nearest common dom block: " << 0
1308 printMBBReference(*SinkBlock) << "\n"); ----
1309 } ----
1310 ----
1311 if (!CanSink) { 0
1312 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "CycleSink: Can't sink instruction.\n"); 0
1313 return false; 0
1314 } ----
1315 if (!SinkBlock) { 0
1316 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "CycleSink: Not sinking, can't find sink block.\n"); 0
1317 return false; 0
1318 } ----
1319 if (SinkBlock == Preheader) { 0
1320 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
1321 dbgs() << "CycleSink: Not sinking, sink block is the preheader\n"); ----
1322 return false; 0
1323 } ----
1324 if (SinkBlock->sizeWithoutDebugLargerThan(SinkLoadInstsPerBlockThreshold)) { 0
1325 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
1326 dbgs() << "CycleSink: Not Sinking, block too large to analyse.\n"); ----
1327 return false; 0
1328 } ----
1329 ----
1330 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "CycleSink: Sinking instruction!\n"); 0
1331 SinkBlock->splice(SinkBlock->SkipPHIsAndLabels(SinkBlock->begin()), Preheader, 0
1332 I); ----
1333 ----
1334 // Conservatively clear any kill flags on uses of sunk instruction ----
1335 for (MachineOperand &MO : I.operands()) { 0
1336 if (MO.isReg() && MO.readsReg()) 0
1337 RegsToClearKillFlags.insert(MO.getReg()); 0
1338 } ----
1339 ----
1340 // The instruction is moved from its basic block, so do not retain the ----
1341 // debug information. ----
1342 assert(!I.isDebugInstr() && "Should not sink debug inst"); 0
1343 I.setDebugLoc(DebugLoc()); 0
1344 return true; 0
1345 } ----
1346 ----
1347 /// SinkInstruction - Determine whether it is safe to sink the specified machine ----
1348 /// instruction out of its current block into a successor. ----
1349 bool MachineSinking::SinkInstruction(MachineInstr &MI, bool &SawStore, 0
1350 AllSuccsCache &AllSuccessors) { ----
1351 // Don't sink instructions that the target prefers not to sink. ----
1352 if (!TII->shouldSink(MI)) 0
1353 return false; 0
1354 ----
1355 // Check if it's safe to move the instruction. ----
1356 if (!MI.isSafeToMove(AA, SawStore)) 0
1357 return false; 0
1358 ----
1359 // Convergent operations may not be made control-dependent on additional ----
1360 // values. ----
1361 if (MI.isConvergent()) 0
1362 return false; 0
1363 ----
1364 // Don't break implicit null checks. This is a performance heuristic, and not ----
1365 // required for correctness. ----
1366 if (SinkingPreventsImplicitNullCheck(MI, TII, TRI)) 0
1367 return false; 0
1368 ----
1369 // FIXME: This should include support for sinking instructions within the ----
1370 // block they are currently in to shorten the live ranges. We often get ----
1371 // instructions sunk into the top of a large block, but it would be better to ----
1372 // also sink them down before their first use in the block. This xform has to ----
1373 // be careful not to *increase* register pressure though, e.g. sinking ----
1374 // "x = y + z" down if it kills y and z would increase the live ranges of y ----
1375 // and z and only shrink the live range of x. ----
1376 ----
1377 bool BreakPHIEdge = false; 0
1378 MachineBasicBlock *ParentBlock = MI.getParent(); 0
1379 MachineBasicBlock *SuccToSinkTo = ----
1380 FindSuccToSinkTo(MI, ParentBlock, BreakPHIEdge, AllSuccessors); 0
1381 ----
1382 // If there are no outputs, it must have side-effects. ----
1383 if (!SuccToSinkTo) 0
1384 return false; 0
1385 ----
1386 // If the instruction to move defines a dead physical register which is live ----
1387 // when leaving the basic block, don't move it because it could turn into a ----
1388 // "zombie" define of that preg. E.g., EFLAGS. () ----
1389 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI.all_defs()) { 0
1390 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
1391 if (Reg == 0 || !Reg.isPhysical()) 0
1392 continue; 0
1393 if (SuccToSinkTo->isLiveIn(Reg)) 0
1394 return false; 0
1395 } ----
1396 ----
1397 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Sink instr " << MI << "\tinto block " << *SuccToSinkTo); 0
1398 ----
1399 // If the block has multiple predecessors, this is a critical edge. ----
1400 // Decide if we can sink along it or need to break the edge. ----
1401 if (SuccToSinkTo->pred_size() > 1) { 0
1402 // We cannot sink a load across a critical edge - there may be stores in ----
1403 // other code paths. ----
1404 bool TryBreak = false; 0
1405 bool Store = ----
1406 MI.mayLoad() ? hasStoreBetween(ParentBlock, SuccToSinkTo, MI) : true; 0
1407 if (!MI.isSafeToMove(AA, Store)) { 0
1408 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " *** NOTE: Won't sink load along critical edge.\n"); 0
1409 TryBreak = true; 0
1410 } ----
1411 ----
1412 // We don't want to sink across a critical edge if we don't dominate the ----
1413 // successor. We could be introducing calculations to new code paths. ----
1414 if (!TryBreak && !DT->dominates(ParentBlock, SuccToSinkTo)) { 0
1415 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " *** NOTE: Critical edge found\n"); 0
1416 TryBreak = true; 0
1417 } ----
1418 ----
1419 // Don't sink instructions into a cycle. ----
1420 if (!TryBreak && CI->getCycle(SuccToSinkTo) && 0
1421 (!CI->getCycle(SuccToSinkTo)->isReducible() || 0
1422 CI->getCycle(SuccToSinkTo)->getHeader() == SuccToSinkTo)) { 0
1423 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " *** NOTE: cycle header found\n"); 0
1424 TryBreak = true; 0
1425 } ----
1426 ----
1427 // Otherwise we are OK with sinking along a critical edge. ----
1428 if (!TryBreak) 0
1429 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Sinking along critical edge.\n"); 0
1430 else { ----
1431 // Mark this edge as to be split. ----
1432 // If the edge can actually be split, the next iteration of the main loop ----
1433 // will sink MI in the newly created block. ----
1434 bool Status = ----
1435 PostponeSplitCriticalEdge(MI, ParentBlock, SuccToSinkTo, BreakPHIEdge); 0
1436 if (!Status) 0
1437 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " *** PUNTING: Not legal or profitable to " 0
1438 "break critical edge\n"); ----
1439 // The instruction will not be sunk this time. ----
1440 return false; 0
1441 } ----
1442 } ----
1443 ----
1444 if (BreakPHIEdge) { 0
1445 // BreakPHIEdge is true if all the uses are in the successor MBB being ----
1446 // sunken into and they are all PHI nodes. In this case, machine-sink must ----
1447 // break the critical edge first. ----
1448 bool Status = PostponeSplitCriticalEdge(MI, ParentBlock, 0
1449 SuccToSinkTo, BreakPHIEdge); ----
1450 if (!Status) 0
1451 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " *** PUNTING: Not legal or profitable to " 0
1452 "break critical edge\n"); ----
1453 // The instruction will not be sunk this time. ----
1454 return false; 0
1455 } ----
1456 ----
1457 // Determine where to insert into. Skip phi nodes. ----
1458 MachineBasicBlock::iterator InsertPos = ----
1459 SuccToSinkTo->SkipPHIsAndLabels(SuccToSinkTo->begin()); 0
1460 if (blockPrologueInterferes(SuccToSinkTo, InsertPos, MI, TRI, TII, MRI)) { 0
1461 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " *** Not sinking: prologue interference\n"); 0
1462 return false; 0
1463 } ----
1464 ----
1465 // Collect debug users of any vreg that this inst defines. ----
1466 SmallVector DbgUsersToSink; 0
1467 for (auto &MO : MI.all_defs()) { 0
1468 if (!MO.getReg().isVirtual()) 0
1469 continue; 0
1470 if (!SeenDbgUsers.count(MO.getReg())) 0
1471 continue; 0
1472 ----
1473 // Sink any users that don't pass any other DBG_VALUEs for this variable. ----
1474 auto &Users = SeenDbgUsers[MO.getReg()]; 0
1475 for (auto &User : Users) { 0
1476 MachineInstr *DbgMI = User.getPointer(); 0
1477 if (User.getInt()) { 0
1478 // This DBG_VALUE would re-order assignments. If we can't copy-propagate ----
1479 // it, it can't be recovered. Set it undef. ----
1480 if (!attemptDebugCopyProp(MI, *DbgMI, MO.getReg())) 0
1481 DbgMI->setDebugValueUndef(); 0
1482 } else { ----
1483 DbgUsersToSink.push_back( 0
1484 {DbgMI, SmallVector(1, MO.getReg())}); 0
1485 } ----
1486 } ----
1487 } ----
1488 ----
1489 // After sinking, some debug users may not be dominated any more. If possible, ----
1490 // copy-propagate their operands. As it's expensive, don't do this if there's ----
1491 // no debuginfo in the program. ----
1492 if (MI.getMF()->getFunction().getSubprogram() && MI.isCopy()) 0
1493 SalvageUnsunkDebugUsersOfCopy(MI, SuccToSinkTo); 0
1494 ----
1495 performSink(MI, *SuccToSinkTo, InsertPos, DbgUsersToSink); 0
1496 ----
1497 // Conservatively, clear any kill flags, since it's possible that they are no ----
1498 // longer correct. ----
1499 // Note that we have to clear the kill flags for any register this instruction ----
1500 // uses as we may sink over another instruction which currently kills the ----
1501 // used registers. ----
1502 for (MachineOperand &MO : MI.all_uses()) 0
1503 RegsToClearKillFlags.insert(MO.getReg()); // Remember to clear kill flags. 0
1504 ----
1505 return true; 0
1506 } 0
1507 ----
1508 void MachineSinking::SalvageUnsunkDebugUsersOfCopy( 0
1509 MachineInstr &MI, MachineBasicBlock *TargetBlock) { ----
1510 assert(MI.isCopy()); 0
1511 assert(MI.getOperand(1).isReg()); 0
1512 ----
1513 // Enumerate all users of vreg operands that are def'd. Skip those that will ----
1514 // be sunk. For the rest, if they are not dominated by the block we will sink ----
1515 // MI into, propagate the copy source to them. ----
1516 SmallVector DbgDefUsers; 0
1517 SmallVector DbgUseRegs; 0
1518 const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MI.getMF()->getRegInfo(); 0
1519 for (auto &MO : MI.all_defs()) { 0
1520 if (!MO.getReg().isVirtual()) 0
1521 continue; 0
1522 DbgUseRegs.push_back(MO.getReg()); 0
1523 for (auto &User : MRI.use_instructions(MO.getReg())) { 0
1524 if (!User.isDebugValue() || DT->dominates(TargetBlock, User.getParent())) 0
1525 continue; 0
1526 ----
1527 // If is in same block, will either sink or be use-before-def. ----
1528 if (User.getParent() == MI.getParent()) 0
1529 continue; 0
1530 ----
1531 assert(User.hasDebugOperandForReg(MO.getReg()) && 0
1532 "DBG_VALUE user of vreg, but has no operand for it?"); ----
1533 DbgDefUsers.push_back(&User); 0
1534 } ----
1535 } ----
1536 ----
1537 // Point the users of this copy that are no longer dominated, at the source ----
1538 // of the copy. ----
1539 for (auto *User : DbgDefUsers) { 0
1540 for (auto &Reg : DbgUseRegs) { 0
1541 for (auto &DbgOp : User->getDebugOperandsForReg(Reg)) { 0
1542 DbgOp.setReg(MI.getOperand(1).getReg()); 0
1543 DbgOp.setSubReg(MI.getOperand(1).getSubReg()); 0
1544 } 0
1545 } ----
1546 } ----
1547 } 0
1548 ----
1549 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
1550 // This pass is not intended to be a replacement or a complete alternative ----
1551 // for the pre-ra machine sink pass. It is only designed to sink COPY ----
1552 // instructions which should be handled after RA. ----
1553 // ----
1554 // This pass sinks COPY instructions into a successor block, if the COPY is not ----
1555 // used in the current block and the COPY is live-in to a single successor ----
1556 // (i.e., doesn't require the COPY to be duplicated). This avoids executing the ----
1557 // copy on paths where their results aren't needed. This also exposes ----
1558 // additional opportunites for dead copy elimination and shrink wrapping. ----
1559 // ----
1560 // These copies were either not handled by or are inserted after the MachineSink ----
1561 // pass. As an example of the former case, the MachineSink pass cannot sink ----
1562 // COPY instructions with allocatable source registers; for AArch64 these type ----
1563 // of copy instructions are frequently used to move function parameters (PhyReg) ----
1564 // into virtual registers in the entry block. ----
1565 // ----
1566 // For the machine IR below, this pass will sink %w19 in the entry into its ----
1567 // successor (%bb.1) because %w19 is only live-in in %bb.1. ----
1568 // %bb.0: ----
1569 // %wzr = SUBSWri %w1, 1 ----
1570 // %w19 = COPY %w0 ----
1571 // Bcc 11, %bb.2 ----
1572 // %bb.1: ----
1573 // Live Ins: %w19 ----
1574 // BL @fun ----
1575 // %w0 = ADDWrr %w0, %w19 ----
1576 // RET %w0 ----
1577 // %bb.2: ----
1578 // %w0 = COPY %wzr ----
1579 // RET %w0 ----
1580 // As we sink %w19 (CSR in AArch64) into %bb.1, the shrink-wrapping pass will be ----
1581 // able to see %bb.0 as a candidate. ----
1582 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
1583 namespace { ----
1584 ----
1585 class PostRAMachineSinking : public MachineFunctionPass { ----
1586 public: ----
1587 bool runOnMachineFunction(MachineFunction &MF) override; ----
1588 ----
1589 static char ID; ----
1590 PostRAMachineSinking() : MachineFunctionPass(ID) {} 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll

1594 AU.setPreservesCFG(); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1595 MachineFunctionPass::getAnalysisUsage(AU); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1596 } 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1597 ----
1598 MachineFunctionProperties getRequiredProperties() const override { 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1599 return MachineFunctionProperties().set( 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1600 MachineFunctionProperties::Property::NoVRegs); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1601 } ----
1602 ----
1603 private: ----
1604 /// Track which register units have been modified and used. ----
1605 LiveRegUnits ModifiedRegUnits, UsedRegUnits; ----
1606 ----
1607 /// Track DBG_VALUEs of (unmodified) register units. Each DBG_VALUE has an ----
1608 /// entry in this map for each unit it touches. The DBG_VALUE's entry ----
1609 /// consists of a pointer to the instruction itself, and a vector of registers ----
1610 /// referred to by the instruction that overlap the key register unit. ----
1611 DenseMap> SeenDbgInstrs; ----
1612 ----
1613 /// Sink Copy instructions unused in the same block close to their uses in ----
1614 /// successors. ----
1615 bool tryToSinkCopy(MachineBasicBlock &BB, MachineFunction &MF, ----
1616 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI, const TargetInstrInfo *TII); ----

1626 static bool aliasWithRegsInLiveIn(MachineBasicBlock &MBB, unsigned Reg, 0
1627 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI) { ----
1628 LiveRegUnits LiveInRegUnits(*TRI); 0
1629 LiveInRegUnits.addLiveIns(MBB); 0
1630 return !LiveInRegUnits.available(Reg); 0
1631 } 0
1632 ----
1633 static MachineBasicBlock * ----
1634 getSingleLiveInSuccBB(MachineBasicBlock &CurBB, 0
1635 const SmallPtrSetImpl &SinkableBBs, ----
1636 unsigned Reg, const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI) { ----
1637 // Try to find a single sinkable successor in which Reg is live-in. ----
1638 MachineBasicBlock *BB = nullptr; 0
1639 for (auto *SI : SinkableBBs) { 0
1640 if (aliasWithRegsInLiveIn(*SI, Reg, TRI)) { 0
1641 // If BB is set here, Reg is live-in to at least two sinkable successors, ----
1642 // so quit. ----
1643 if (BB) 0
1644 return nullptr; 0
1645 BB = SI; 0
1646 } ----
1647 } ----
1648 // Reg is not live-in to any sinkable successors. ----
1649 if (!BB) 0
1650 return nullptr; 0
1651 ----
1652 // Check if any register aliased with Reg is live-in in other successors. ----
1653 for (auto *SI : CurBB.successors()) { 0
1654 if (!SinkableBBs.count(SI) && aliasWithRegsInLiveIn(*SI, Reg, TRI)) 0
1655 return nullptr; 0
1656 } ----
1657 return BB; 0
1658 } ----
1659 ----
1660 static MachineBasicBlock * ----
1661 getSingleLiveInSuccBB(MachineBasicBlock &CurBB, 0
1662 const SmallPtrSetImpl &SinkableBBs, ----
1663 ArrayRef DefedRegsInCopy, ----
1664 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI) { ----
1665 MachineBasicBlock *SingleBB = nullptr; 0
1666 for (auto DefReg : DefedRegsInCopy) { 0
1667 MachineBasicBlock *BB = ----
1668 getSingleLiveInSuccBB(CurBB, SinkableBBs, DefReg, TRI); 0
1669 if (!BB || (SingleBB && SingleBB != BB)) 0
1670 return nullptr; 0
1671 SingleBB = BB; 0
1672 } ----
1673 return SingleBB; 0
1674 } ----
1675 ----
1676 static void clearKillFlags(MachineInstr *MI, MachineBasicBlock &CurBB, 0
1677 SmallVectorImpl &UsedOpsInCopy, ----
1678 LiveRegUnits &UsedRegUnits, ----
1679 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI) { ----
1680 for (auto U : UsedOpsInCopy) { 0
1681 MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(U); 0
1682 Register SrcReg = MO.getReg(); 0
1683 if (!UsedRegUnits.available(SrcReg)) { 0
1684 MachineBasicBlock::iterator NI = std::next(MI->getIterator()); 0
1685 for (MachineInstr &UI : make_range(NI, CurBB.end())) { 0
1686 if (UI.killsRegister(SrcReg, TRI)) { 0
1687 UI.clearRegisterKills(SrcReg, TRI); 0
1688 MO.setIsKill(true); 0
1689 break; 0
1690 } ----
1691 } ----
1692 } ----
1693 } ----
1694 } 0
1695 ----
1696 static void updateLiveIn(MachineInstr *MI, MachineBasicBlock *SuccBB, 0
1697 SmallVectorImpl &UsedOpsInCopy, ----
1698 SmallVectorImpl &DefedRegsInCopy) { ----
1699 MachineFunction &MF = *SuccBB->getParent(); 0
1700 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI = MF.getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo(); 0
1701 for (unsigned DefReg : DefedRegsInCopy) 0
1702 for (MCPhysReg S : TRI->subregs_inclusive(DefReg)) 0
1703 SuccBB->removeLiveIn(S); 0
1704 for (auto U : UsedOpsInCopy) { 0
1705 Register SrcReg = MI->getOperand(U).getReg(); 0
1706 LaneBitmask Mask; 0
1707 for (MCRegUnitMaskIterator S(SrcReg, TRI); S.isValid(); ++S) { 0
1708 Mask |= (*S).second; 0
1709 } ----
1710 SuccBB->addLiveIn(SrcReg, Mask.any() ? Mask : LaneBitmask::getAll()); 0
1711 } ----
1712 SuccBB->sortUniqueLiveIns(); 0
1713 } 0
1714 ----
1715 static bool hasRegisterDependency(MachineInstr *MI, 0
1716 SmallVectorImpl &UsedOpsInCopy, ----
1717 SmallVectorImpl &DefedRegsInCopy, ----
1718 LiveRegUnits &ModifiedRegUnits, ----
1719 LiveRegUnits &UsedRegUnits) { ----
